data.enText: to do or achieve what was hoped for or expected

data.chText: 实现梦想 / 抱负；发挥潜力

data.enText: to do or have what is required or necessary

data.chText: 履行职责 / 义务 / 诺言
data.enText: to fulfil a duty/an obligation/a promise

data.chText: 执行协定条款 / 条件
data.enText: to fulfil the terms/conditions of an agreement

data.chText: 没有一个候选人完全符合这个职位的标准。
data.enText: No candidate fulfils all the criteria for this position.
to have a particular role or purpose

data.chText: 幼儿园应该起到为儿童进小学作准备的作用。
data.enText: Nursery schools should fulfil the function of preparing children for school.
to make sb feel happy and satisfied with what they are doing or have done

data.chText: 我需要一份真正令我感到满足的工作。
data.enText: I need a job that really fulfils me.

data.chText: 他通过绘画充分发挥了自己的才能。
data.enText: He was able to fulfil himself through his painting.

ex.chText: 那个急诊手术是什么时候做的？
ex.enText: When was that emergency operation performed?

ex.chText: 专家对调查数据进行了分析。
ex.enText: Experts performed an analysis of the survey data.

synonyms.bx: 尤指做困难或有用的事情。

ex.chText: 她认为进行调查是搜集所需信息的最好方式。
ex.enText: In her opinion, conducting a survey is the best way to collect the information needed.

ex.chText: 他想知道如何进行科学实验。
ex.enText: He wanted to know how to conduct science experiments.

synonyms.bx: 尤指为获取信息或证实某事而进行某一活动或过程。

ex.chText: 他们正在实施一个护理计划。
ex.enText: They are executing a nursing care plan.

ex.chText: 这一秘密计划实施得很巧妙。
ex.enText: The plot was very cleverly executed.

ex.chText: 成员国必须履行条约所规定的义务。
ex.enText: It is necessary for the member states to fulfil their obligations under the treaty.

ex.chText: 作为一名教师，恪尽职守很重要。
ex.enText: As a teacher, it is important for you to fulfil your role.

ex.chText: 这些设备未能符合安全要求。
ex.enText: These pieces of equipment failed to fulfil safety requirements.

synonyms.bx: 指做要求或必须做的事情，如履行职责、义务等；也可指满足必要或应有的条件或要求，如达到标准等。

tr: fill or meet a want or need

example: execute the decision of the people

tr: meet the requirements or expectations of

value.def: If you fulfil something such as a promise, dream, or hope, you do what you said or hoped you would do.

example.ex: President Kaunda fulfilled his promise of announcing a date for the referendum.
example.tran: 卡翁达总统兑现了他的承诺，宣布了全民公决的日期。

value.def: To fulfil a task, role, or requirement means to do or be what is required, necessary, or expected.

example.ex: Without them you will not be able to fulfil the tasks you have before you...
example.tran: 没有他们你将无法完成面临的任务。

example.ex: All the necessary conditions were fulfilled.
example.tran: 所有必要的条件都满足了。

value.def: If something fulfils you, or if you fulfil yourself, you feel happy and satisfied with what you are doing or with what you have achieved.

example.ex: The war was the biggest thing in her life and nothing after that quite fulfilled her...
example.tran: 这场战争是她生命中最重大的事件，从那以后再没有什么让她特别有成就感的了。

example.ex: They don't like the idea that women can fulfil themselves without the assistance of a man.
example.tran: 他们不喜欢那种女人没有男人的帮助仍会有所成就的想法。

value.tran: 满足;使满意;使有成就感

example.ex: She has courageously continued to lead a fulfilled life...
example.tran: 她一直勇敢地坚持着充实满足的生活。

example.ex: I feel more fulfilled doing this than I've ever done.
example.tran: 做这件事让我比以往任何时候都感到满足。

example.ex: I found it all very fulfilling.
example.tran: 我发觉一切都令人感到非常满足。
